===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|彑|米|糸|廾|t1=head|t2=rice|t3=silk|t4=two hands|ls=ic|ls2=psc|c1=p|c2=s|c3=s|c4=s}} – a bird or slave with its wings or hands tied, offered for sacrifice with two hands. The bird or slave's head is represented by {{zh-l|*彑}}, the body now by {{zh-l|*米}} (no connection to “rice”), the string that ties the wings or hands by {{zh-l|*糸}}, and the two hands by {{zh-l|*廾}}. The {{zh-l|*彑}} component is stated to be a phonetic in ''Shuowen''.

